03/11/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A survey of Transparency International's Centre for Provision of Legal Aid in Combating Corruption says corruption in BiH is most prevalent among public procurement, inspection and privatisation authorities. During a news conference Tuesday (2 November), officials presented data from August to October 2004 which indicated the centre had learned of 2,500 corruption cases, most of which involved inspectors with the state administration. In 12 of the cases, the centre sought help from the Office of the High Representative. (Fena - 02/11/04)
